{"author":"Claude","data":{"alias":"geologic-epidermic-thrush","description":"## Why\n`CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID` is exposed as an env var ONLY in the remote/cloud runner; the\nLOCAL Claude Code CLI does not export it (unshipped feature request). Without a shim the\nfeature silently no-ops for local-CLI users — the most common case. The robust, harness-\nagnostic capture (mirroring claude-mem) is a SessionStart hook that reads the hook's\n`session_id` from stdin and exports it as the portable `REBAR_SESSION_ID`.\n\n## What\nShip a small Claude Code SessionStart hook that reads `session_id` from the hook stdin\nenvelope and writes `REBAR_SESSION_ID=<id>` via the `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` mechanism, plus a\none-line install snippet. Must be idempotent and fire-and-forget (no daemon, no shared\nstate — see epic gotcha G2).\n\n## Scope\n- IN: the hook script, install docs, a note that it must be session-scoped (not exported\n  into a shell profile — gotcha G3), and handling of resume/continue double-fire (G1).\n- OUT: Codex/Cursor shims (S6); the read/record core (S1-S3).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A SessionStart hook exports `REBAR_SESSION_ID` from the hook `session_id`.\n- [ ] With the hook installed, a local-CLI claim records `claimed_session` (end-to-end).\n- [ ] Hook is idempotent and does not error on resume/continue (documents the id-instability\n      caveat G1).\n- [ ] Install instructions documented; guidance to keep it session-scoped (not in profile).\n\n## Depends on\n- S1 (the `REBAR_SESSION_ID` contract).\n","id":"ec5c-bd06-aa49-42d0","parent_id":"38ec-5f12-fdf5-4340","priority":3,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Claude Code SessionStart hook shim to populate REBAR_SESSION_ID in the local CLI"},"env_id":"724d9d0c-bc4c-4cc4-b96b-1a19356102e2","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783481181760763706,"uuid":"f13163b4-78c4-4e67-8554-c13d598e9396"}